IP addresses can be in IPv4 or IPv6 format - auth_data Sets the HTTP POST data, that will be forwarded to the authentication service, to the provided data. - auth_parameters The HTTP GET parameters that will be forwarded to the authentication service to the provided parameters. - auth_type The type of the "Custom Authentication" service that will be used. entries.description: Authenticates users by their Steam Account. Pass L"ticket=[ticket]" to setParameters().
entries.name: AUTH_STEAM

entries.description: Authenticates users by their Facebook Account. Pass L"token=[token]" to setParameters().
entries.name: AUTH_FACEBOOK

entries.description: Authenticates users by their Oculus Account. Pass L"userid=[userid]&nonce=[nonce]" to setParameters().
entries.name: AUTH_OCULUS

entries.description: Authenticates users by their PSN Account. Pass L"token=[token]&env=[env]&userName=[userName]" to setParameters().
entries.name: AUTH_PLAYSTATION_4

entries.description: Authenticates users by their XBox Network Account. Pass the XSTS token to setData().
entries.name: AUTH_XBOX

entries.description: Authenticates users by their HTC Viveport Account and user token. Pass L"userToken=[userToken]" to setParameters().
entries.name: AUTH_VIVEPORT

entries.description: Authenticates users by their Nintendo Account. Pass L"token=[token]&appversion=[appversion]" to setParameters(). The appversion is optional.
entries.name: AUTH_NINTENDO_SWITCH

entries.description: Authenticates users by their PSN Account. Pass L"token=[token]&env=[env]&userName=[userName]" to setParameters().
entries.name: AUTH_PLAYSTATION_5

entries.description: Authenticates users by their Epic Online Services (EOS) Account. Pass L"token=[token]&ownershipToken=[ownershipToken]" to setParameters(). The ownershipToken is optional.
entries.name: AUTH_EPIC

entries.description: Authenticates users by their Facebook Account. Pass L"token=[token]" to setParameters().
entries.name: AUTH_FACEBOOK_GAMING

entries.description: Photon Cloud and for self-hosted Photon 5 or higher Server instances
entries.name: SERVER_TYPE_NAME_SERVER

entries.description: Fills up rooms (oldest first) to get players together as fast as possible. Default. Makes most sense with MaxPlayers > 0 and games that can only start with more players.
entries.name: MATCHMAKINGMODE_FILL_ROOM

entries.description: Distributes players across available rooms sequentially but takes filters into account. Without filters, rooms get players evenly distributed.
entries.name: MATCHMAKINGMODE_SERIAL_MATCHING

entries.description: Joins a (fully) random room. Expected properties must match, but aside from this, any available room might be selected.
entries.name: MATCHMAKINGMODE_RANDOM_MATCHING

entries.description: This lobby type is used unless another lobby type is specified. Room lists will be sent and Client::opJoinRandomRoom() can filter by matching properties.
entries.name: LOBBYTYPE_DEFAULT

entries.description: This lobby type lists rooms like type DEFAULT but  SQL-like "where" clauses for filtering can be used with Client::opJoinRandomRoom(). This allows 'bigger', 'less', 'or' and 'and' combinations.
entries.name: LOBBYTYPE_SQL_LOBBY

entries.description: This lobby does not send room lists. It is only used for Client::opJoinRandomRoom(). It keeps rooms available for matchmaking for a while even when there are only inactive users left.
entries.name: LOBBYTYPE_ASYNC_RANDOM_LOBBY

entries.description: Do not create any 2p2 connections between the clients. This is the default.
entries.name: DIRECTMODE_NONE

entries.description: Each client establishes a direct connection with every other client inside the room.
entries.name: DIRECTMODE_ALL_TO_OTHERS

entries.description: The master client establishes a direct connection with every other client inside the room. All other clients only establish a direct connection with the master client but not with each other.
entries.name: DIRECTMODE_MASTER_TO_OTHERS

entries.description: Each client establishes a direct connection with every client inside the room, including itself.
entries.name: DIRECTMODE_ALL_TO_ALL

entries.description: The master client establishes a direct connection with every client inside the room, including itself. All other clients only establish a direct connection with the master client but not with each other.
entries.name: DIRECTMODE_MASTER_TO_ALL
